## Revised Architecture

```
Audio Session
   ↓
[ Base EQ ]  ← AutoEQ preset OR flat (existing)
   ↓
[ Custom Tuning delta ]  ← user bass/vocals/treble (existing)
   ↓
[ SPATIAL AUDIO ENGINE ]  ← NEW — fully independent
    Layer A: Psychoacoustic Coloring
      - Pan impression: slight side-channel ILD simulation via treble shelf
      - Pinna notch shaping: slight 6–8 kHz dip + 9–12 kHz cut (directional cue)
      - Torso warmth: subtle 200–400 Hz body/warmth presence
    Layer B: Depth / Envelopment (FDN Reverb)
      - Software Feedback Delay Network (short, parameterized)
      - Controls: room size (RT60), wet/dry blend
   ↓
Clamp → Output
```

**Model:** Dolby Atmos' real-world approach — **~85% amplitude/EQ coloring + ~15% HRTF-inspired spectral shaping**.
Full HRTF convolution (the remaining theoretical ideal) is architecturally out of scope on Android's `AudioEffect` API without raw PCM access.

